column8: Uh, so, did everybody miss me...?
No wonder they don't like you.
You've taught me everything I know. Other than how to fend for myself, I owe Achilles that.
Wish I could be there to see your face.
At least he likes the dog.
He's fast asleep. How long has he been up...? Whatever, I should go.
You keep an eye on Father for me, boy. Don't let him sour up everyone's mood.
I'm back, Room, did you miss me?
Oh come on it's not that bad is it?
Mother... I wonder... will you even remember me?
If I sit down I won't want to get back up.
Not as comfy as it looks.
...This is the cheeriest thing I think I've heard from him.

So mate, you know Eurydice? Well I just happened to run into her out there. Asked me to let you know that she can always hear your songs, no matter how far apart you are. Seemed rather sweet of her, I have to say.
Smack guys against walls. Sound advice as ever, Skelly.
Look for the perfect opportunity to unleash my much-feared temper. Check.
Happy to be of service there, now you just keep watching that big old pool of blood for us, all right?
I... can't get used to that.
Well, time to go get killed again.
A new addition to the old collection.
I can do better than that.
Like to think I learned something back there.
Those two are at it again. I'd best stay out of this.
...Looks like these two are at it again. I'd better stay out of this.
...Looks like these two are busy making friends. I'd better stay out of this.
Mischief, me? I was just going to have a little look through Father's stuff.
Lower your voice, old man, I'm trying to be sneaky here...!
I said, shut up, old man!
She has, Nyx. I am grateful that you put us into contact, and explained to her the situation that I'm in.
Why, um, I'm just on my way right now, Dusa, but, some other time, for sure! I think I'd like that, really!
That's... I'm sorry to hear that. Thank you for letting me know. She sounds truly wonderful.
Mate, if you don't mind, I'd love it if you told me more about your muse. Eurydice.
Orpheus here believes absolutely everything. At first I thought it mean, telling tall tales to him, but it seems to be the only way to cheer him up.
Nothing for me back there anyway.
Orpheus here hasn't sung a song in I don't know how long. Father basically ignores him now.
Don't worry, mate. Father can't make you sing if you don't want to. I might be gone a while, so... take care of yourself.
Thanks for all your hard work...!
...Wow. She didn't even wait for my response.
Better than I could have possibly imagined, Nyx. I'm grateful that you found me such a fine replacement.
What can I say, I try.
I want to go lie down.
What are those shades muttering about.
Those shades are always milling about.
How many times has it been?
How many times has it been now?
As many chances as it takes.
Just need to keep at it.
I don't know what to say, mate.
Must be something worth a damn in here.
I'm standing right here, old man.
You know I can hear you, old man.
More ways to grow my strength.
I'll have to come back later.
You have my thanks, Lord Ares.
Showed that stupid Hydra, at least.
Think that's about as far as I can get for now.
I'll get you for that, Meg.
Least we can look forward to the grand reopening.
Hey how'd you get in here?

Orpheus, you're back! I guess you've heard the latest with me, then. But I'm all right, just, might be gone a while, sorting some things out. So take care, and don't worry, mate. Father can't make you sing if you don't want to.
Achilles must have been incredible back when he was alive.
Aphrodite herself. Wonder if I could get this signed.
Bronze weapons... made crudely, but they had the right idea.
Always wanted my own scrying pool.
Cheer up, boy, it'll be all right.
Don't even think about it, boy.
No sign of Cerberus for now.
What are they on about now.
What are these shades up to now?
What do these shades have to say for themselves.
I can escape through that pink window there.
My escape route's back the other way.
I can escape from the courtyard back there.
Urgh, you win this round, Meg.
All those wretches got the best of me.
Got just a little greedy I suppose.
That's what I get for messing with a trove.
Rngh, that trove should've been mine.
That did not go as planned.
I've got to stop walking on spikes like that.
Damn dart traps shot me all to hell.
I really shouldn't step on dart traps anymore...
I hate it when they fight.
They're at it again... because of me.
My faith is prone to shakiness at times.
Ladies night I guess. Or day? I don't know.
That's probably bad news for me.
There isn't much for us to talk about.
Your faith in me means a lot, Nyx.
Thank you, though I've much to learn as yet.
I think I turned out OK.
Just couldn't take the heat back there.
Urgh that was not a pleasant journey.
The Mirror... at last I see myself for what I am.
Every facet of the Mirror, now within my grasp.
Please accept from me this humble gift, O Master Chaos.
I'd better try some other time.
They seem busy at the moment.
Doesn't seem like a good time.
They're in the middle of something.
I'm through with Father's dirty work.
Let's see what we can do with this place.
Father always said never to take the easy way.
I can make life even more miserable here.
I'm not cleared to do that.
Wretches of the Underworld, take heed.
That ought to liven things up.
What's the worst that could happen?
What's life without a little pain.
What's with the contract in my chambers, Father? You offering me a job?
Urgh, that blasted giant gorgon head.
Eugh, not a word of this to Dusa...
Augh, gorgons, what can you do...
I see. I'm sorry to have troubled you.
Give me the best deal you've got.
Wretched Broker, what's new, my friend?
This Broker sure reminds me of a guy who's killed me once or twice.
You trying to fleece me here?
Nothing left to trade for now.
I'll have to come back later.
Fresh out of stock for now.
It's not all it's cracked up to be.

Let me guess... they want me to fight all the way through the Underworld, having used the Pact of Punishment in my bedchambers to make the going even more treacherous than it already is, and if I succeed, they'll reward me with some sort of useless trinket?
Yes, a little bit, if you must know.
I'll temper my expectations just in case.
Another Skelly statue. Why am I not surprised.
I guess they're stuck here then just like we are.
It's another statue of you, Skelly.
We certainly have, Mate. And we certainly do.
I need to do what now?
I need to fire up the Pact of Punishment to reveal this.
I need to use the Pact back in my Chambers.
Sounds like the Pact in my Chambers is the only way I'm going to earn this thing.
The Pact of Punishment is the key to this, huh.
It's some sort of ridiculous challenge huh.
Someone's trying to goad me into using the Pact of Punishment.
I'll have to survive the worst the Underworld has to offer before I can open this.
I've yet to earn the right to look upon whatever this is.
I'll need to survive the horrors of the Underworld first.
I have to earn this I guess.
The Pact is fired up, just have to earn this.
Earning this is going to be tough.
Finally did it, what do I get?
I earned this fair and square.
I have a feeling I know what this is...
Thank you, thank you, everyone, you're too kind.
Always wanted a statue of Skelly in my honor.
Breathtaking detail in the rib-cage area.
The subtlety of the expression is a fascinating touch.
There's so much tension in the shape of it.
The raw emotion there is rather striking isn't it.
I practically can feel the anguish in this piece.
The use of light and shadow is exceptional.
I think it represents... the plight of mortal life.
I think it signifies the duality in all of us.
I think it speaks to how our pride can be our downfall?
How did they get the fingerbones to look so real.
Truly the work of a great master.
Didn't catch the name of the artist...
Dionysus and I appreciate it, mate.
Your methods didn't seem to do the trick.
I'll use it to the best of my ability, sir.
I... fear is for the weak.
Guess Than must be at work.
Hey, Than... come split this with me for a bit. The coast is clear. The work can wait.
You take care, too, Thanatos. Be seeing you.
I will. You're right as always, sir.
Augh, that wasn't very kind of her, was it.
Unf, I guess Alecto wins this round.
I much prefer Meg's whip, I have to say...
Not even Than could get me out of that one.
Than tried to help at least.
Than won't be happy about that.
Than tried his best at least...
He's like an annoying little brother to me.
Nghh, that bull hits rather hard.
Ungh, I want a rematch, now.
Rmm, how could I lose to him.
This is a real honor, Hypnos. Thanks?
Achilles, please... are you certain that I mustn't talk to Father about the pact you signed for Patroclus? He thinks that you abandoned him.
And then, we'll both find out.
They should have asked the expert I suppose.
I'm counting that one as a victory.
I'll make it out of here yet.
That ought to make Theseus shut it for a bit.
Feels like it's been a while, everybody.
Urgh, well that was pretty good, all in all.
He shouldn't, sir. And neither should you.
I see. I think. I'm grateful for it, sir.
Sorry, Father. I'm not afraid of you.
Angh, he's strong, I'll give him that.
Ough, he's tough for an old man.
Guh, how am I going to beat him.
Mmph, got me again, damn it.
Augh, I'll get you for this, Father.
Well, this is going to be awkward.
Cerberus must be on duty still.
Cerberus must still be back up top.
Cerberus is still at work I guess.
Guess I'll keep fighting you just for the sake of it then.
Always have more pets for the greatest boy.
How's my favorite boy doing, huh?
You've always been there for me, boy.
You are the best, you know that, don't you, boy?
My mean old father's nice to you at least, isn't he, boy?
You had enough to eat lately, haven't you boy?
You like it when you get pets like this, don't you boy.
You want more pets, I got more pets here, boy.
Always feel better talking to you, boy.
You don't let anybody in or out of this place, do you, boy.
More pets are certainly in order here.
You're my good boy! Yes you are.
That thing doesn't look particularly comfortable.
I'd bring some for you if I could!
Don't want to talk about it.
Why don't you ask Father when he's back.
See you up at the Temple then, I guess.
Until such place and time, then.
Father and Cerberus must still be up there.
No sign of Cerberus or Father.
Oh, it's no trouble at all.
Didn't think things could get any more awkward with her.
In the mean time, I'll take good care of them.
Not a concern, just a morbid curiosity.
That's why he's stuck here, huh.
Least we have a backup singer if we need one.
I guess there are a lot of gemstones here.
Ever since? It's not been that long.
It's supposed to be updated every so often but it's always Thanatos.
I wish I did not know that.
I'll have to get to the bottom of this later.
You're not making this easy, Orpheus.
The Fates can't be that cruel...
Take all the time you need, mate.
Great to hear it. I can only imagine.
I guess I can see that. Cheers.
It's all right. Father can't make you sing if you don't want to.
Thanks for the impromptu lesson, mate.
You're doing wonderfully at it, mate.
...Did he make fun of me just now?
Hey what happened to the Pact of Punishment?
The exit... that's a Pact of Punishment on it.
Is that the Pact of Punishment...?
I need to use the Pact on my way out.
The Pact over there is the key to revealing this.
Who's that new shade there next to Father?
Something's different about that shade next to Father.
As likely an explanation as any I guess.
I should go check it out.
If I'm to keep seeing my chamber walls, they might as well not be completely barren.
Hey, they're my bedchambers, I can have whatever wall-scrolls I want.
Should help make my messy chambers even messier.
Should make a nice-enough addition to my chambers.
Ah yes, more comfortable seating I shall never use.
This one's for all the solitary shades hanging around forever in the lounge.
Anything to liven things up even the slightest bit around here.
What is it about fountains that makes everything feel a little fancier?
Always hoped we'd have a fountain here precisely in that location.
Who am I to stop the shades there in the lounge from cooking up whatever it is they're making?
Whew. It's a big job, having to sweep up after Cerberus sheds everywhere.
This ought to make the lounge a little more presentable. Until Cerberus wrecks it again.
Should make the climate in the lounge a bit more comfortable for some of us.
There's not much on the menu in the lounge but maybe this will help.
Huh maybe I can use this to avoid Father's withering gaze and unwanted feedback.
How about a moody blue color of some sort for the drapery there.
Perhaps a rich green hue for the drapery will feel a little homelier?
A crimson color for the drapery is sure to be a better fit for the decor.
You know what, I changed my mind about the drapery.
I miss the way things used to be, dear Drapery.
The time has come once more to modify the drapery.
Helps keep things colorful to change the drapery from time to time.
Either those curtains go, or I do.
This ought to help Orpheus keep his boundless libraries of music in order. Just have to fill it in.
Paid in full up front, let's see what we get!
House Contractor, I have a new job for you.
All right, House Contractor, go do your thing.
Let's lighten things up a little around here.
Let's see how this one turns out.
All right, let's see what we got.
This should help liven the mood a bit.
One more embellishment for the old House.
Should check the music stand to hear this one.
Another piece for the music stand.
More music for the music stand is always good.
Can hardly wait to listen to this one.
More substantive material for the music stand.
More music to soothe the senses.
Not going to say no to more music.
New music for the music stand? OK!
Any new updates for the House?
Let's see what the Contractor has.
Pick something up for the House maybe?
What can we do for this stodgy House.
Best give this shade some work.
I'll have to come back later.
Looks like Father's changed the terms of our relationship.
It can tell I have Varatha.
Maybe I ought to risk it.
New stipulations added to the Pact.
There's a new condition on the Pact.
That's as bad as this gets.
That's as far as it goes.
That's as much Heat as I can get from this.
Coronacht... is this what you really are?
Aegis... you are as old as time...
Varatha... you once were Father's spear...
Exagryph... you're telling me your secrets...
Let me see you now for what you truly are.
You are bound to me, and I am your host.
Let's test the bond between us.
What are the limits of your power?
You're no mere weapon, are you.
Far greater gods than I once wielded you.
You are as multifaceted as anyone I know.
Let me see into your past.
Grant me the aspect of Nemesis!
Grant me the aspect of Poseidon!
Grant me the aspect of Hera!
Grant me the aspect of Chiron!
Grant me the aspect of Achilles himself!
Grant me the aspect of my father!
Grant me the aspect of Zeus!
Grant me the aspect of Chaos!
Grant me the aspect of Hestia!
Grant me the aspect of Eris!
I need to track down more Chthonic Keys.
I can find more of those keys if I engage the Pact...
I'll find more of those keys if I use the Pact...
I don't have enough Chthonic Keys...
All right, then, keep your secrets...
I need more Chthonic Keys for this.
Begging your pardon, my good Shade.
Ugh, more Fury Sisters than I bargained for...
Urgh, that's one sister too many...
Mmph, that didn't seem particularly fair.
Ungh, I guess I should be flattered in a way...
Augh, don't the Furies have somebody else they could be torturing...
That's as far as we can go.
I see everything about you now.
Care to join me out there?
Never made it up there myself!
Prices are a little steep there, I must say.
I can't afford any of this.
What am I, composed entirely of gemstones?
Maybe you'll have something more affordable next time.
How's that knife set working out?
Those spices working out all right?
Cooking's one way to pass the time.
This is the most decadent thing I've ever bought.
I won't ever grow weary of this!
I won't ever grow weary of this... will I?
Need more of those, so here.
Just what I was looking for.
It's all right, wasn't hungry anyway.
Won't get extra Bounties this way, but why not.
Blowing out the Heat Gauge isn't going to do me any favors here.
Don't need to turn the Heat Gauge so high to earn those Bounties.
Won't get Bounties any faster with this extra Heat.
Time to put in extra work for those Bounties.
If it's Bounties I'm after, no need to turn the Heat up this high.
This one, Contractor. Ought to make the Underworld a better place, I think.
Let's make it happen. I'll have to keep an eye out for this next I'm out there.
I like the sound of this. Work approved and here's the fee, Contractor sir!
Here you go! I'll be on the lookout for this when I'm in the area.
Here! The Underworld could always use a little extra renovating, right?
I like the sound of this one here, Contractor sir. Go make it happen!
Work is approved, upon my father's name! Not like he's paying any heed.
I'm hereby authorizing this expenditure! And I look forward to seeing the result.
House Contractor, my good shade, I've yet another job for your distinguished team.
Let's go with this assignment, Contractor! My father surely would approve.
This looks to be an excellent investment, Contractor! Go on and make it so.
The ever-shifting chambers of the Underworld ought be a little livelier with this.
I'd say our court musician's suffered quite enough. Besides, I miss his cheerful disposition.
The Fated List of Minor Prophecies... that sounds somewhat exciting, I suppose.
Hey that must be the Fated List...
Rrng, where can I get armor like that?
Nngh, how do I get through all that armor?
Oof, turns out I can like Theseus even less.
Mmrn, Theseus can't just run over me like that...
Augh, how come he gets the Macedonian...
Ugh, well then I guess I missed my deadline.
Oomph, that was a little too much Heat.
Nrgh, ran out of time back there I guess.
Hey Meg, I was just thinking that you really shouldn't settle for the run-of-the-mill contraband that I've been handing off to you. I got you something absolutely scandalous this time.
I see. Take all the time you need.
Hoh now let's not get ahead of ourselves, Meg.
Then no more tricks like that again.
Skelly, mate... this what I think it is?
Nyx, the latest renovations from the Contractor... Father told me you've been supervising all of that. Look, just between us, and I'll not speak of it again, but... thanks. So much.
Is this all that the Fates have planned for me...?
Let's have a look at the old Fated List.
What do the Three Fates have in mind?
Something new in store for me?
Something's added to the Fated List.
Who am I to question Fate?
I can escape through that sinister window there.
Looks like Father's not going to make this easy on me.
No getting out of that one.
I'll have to live with that.
...Each time I die like that, I come back stronger.
Must be the Fated List there on my desk...
I never thought of it like that.
Didn't know you saw it that way.
What, Thanatos, is this... you're really giving Mort to me? I... I'm deeply honored!
Skelly, mate! You really shouldn't have. Do you have any idea how hard-to-find this is?!
Sir, is this a mint-condition Shady you just gave to me?! I'm so grateful. I will keep him safe!
An eternity of hard labor seems a little much for Sisyphus. Let's lighten up his burden, then, shall we?
I should check in with the House Contractor.
Ought to spend some of these gems with the House Contractor.
Wonder what jobs the House Contractor has available.
I got a new Companion! I can bring it along with my other Keepsake.
Can't get out of here till I turn up the Heat.
Thanks, Achilles. That means a lot.
Oh no, not this determinism thing again...
Should turn around. My escape route's in the courtyard I just left.
Someone's at the desk next to the throne...
Some sort of special offer for me, my good Shade?
Work authorized! A fountain chamber in the depths of Tartarus sounds like an excellent idea.
I wouldn't mind their help I guess!
Well! I wasn't about to drink it.
Sell it or keep it, huh.
That it did most definitely, sir.
Thank you for the advice, Achilles, sir.
I'm not the god of anything, all right?
I will not let that happen.
Nyx, I don't suppose you know where Megaera came from...? Is it really true she has no parents, whatsoever...? You've always taken care of all of us, and so... I was just wondering, I guess.
I need to get my hands on more Ambrosia.
Don't have enough Nectar for this.
I need to turn up the Heat.
Not getting out of here without more Heat.
I need to add Conditions to the Pact.
I need to change the Pact before I go.
I have to modify the Pact.
I need to add more Heat.
Hey that's the Court Musician's sentence, long past due...
Achilles thinks that I'm the... god of blood?
The Fated List of Minor Prophecies...
A prophecy's been added to the List.
This one's for you, Three Fates!
Pleasure doing business with you, Fates.
That's what I was afraid of.
I'll have to try that, thanks.
Achilles, something has awakened in Varatha... it revealed to me a form I'd never seen. Wielded by a great bearded warrior called Guan Yu. Handsomely dressed! That's no Greek name, is it...
Wait, you mean this is an aspect from a time that's yet to come? That hurts my head. Why would it show up all of a sudden, now?
Good thing they're on my side.
You don't like it when I pet your other heads, huh? No!
Here boy, just as long as one of your three heads enjoy these pets!
If I don't pet your other heads, don't bite my arm off, deal?
Not everybody knows exactly how to give you pets and live to tell of it, right, boy?
Grant me the aspect of Guan Yu!
I need more Darkness for that.
This Ambrosia ought to pay for that.
That's too good a deal to pass up.
I like the sound of this. Work approved and here's the fee, good Contractor!
I like the sound of this one here, good Contractor. Go make it happen!
Contractor, I would ask that you pursue this job. I'll be excited to see the result!
Your asking price, good Contractor. Well worth the fruits of your hard work, I'm sure.
Since Father's not paying us any heed, what say with go with this assignment, Contractor?
I grant you funding and autonomy to do this job upon your earliest convenience, Contractor.
All right! If this isn't a good expenditure of resources, then I don't know what is.
On my authority, I'd like it if you did this job for me, is that all right?
I think we'll go with this.
Let's go with this one, then.
This should be good I think.
Well, I don't see why not.
No need to overthink this one I guess.
It's not our custom to hang brightly colored things in here, though why not try these on for size.
Hanging bright-colored explosives all about my chambers strikes me as a fine idea!
I positively cannot wait to see what sorts of foul creatures I'll dredge up with this!
A fine hallway requires a fine rug, I always say! I say it sometimes...
Oh we absolutely need to get this rug, right over there.
By my decree, this House is not a house without this rug.
If there's a finer rug to set back there, I'll likely end up getting it as well.
What time is it? That's right: Rug-switching time!
Hrm I don't know let's try a different rug.
Let's try a different rug there, if you please.
I've had a change of heart about that rug if you don't mind.
I think we both know that it's time to change the rug.
If anybody needs to see their own reflection down the hall, well, now they can!
Let us hereby have better seating, on which I shall never rest, you mark my words!
We'll have only the finest artwork in this House, and I shall be the self-appointed judge!
It seems my princely duty to commission this fine portrait of myself!
Since this is Father's House it's only fair the walls be slathered with his sour look.
I've no idea who this is but she's so elegant she ought adorn these halls, if you ask me!
This piece has the power to embarrass several members of this House all in one swoop.
Oh gods, am I becoming hopelessly obsessed with Theseus...?
Every self-respecting House needs a portrait of a girl from Crete.
I'd like to see the depths of Tartarus adorn those walls back there!
This artful piece of terrifying Asphodel should add some atmosphere.
I've not seen the famous Heracles about, and so, let's have a marble effigy of him, instead!
A commemorative hammer adds a touch of elegance to any gloomy hall.
Father always wanted a sundial, though that aside, let's have a sundial back there, posthaste!
I'm oddly smitten with this green-tinged orb. Who wouldn't be?
Let's switch things up on that display back there.
I think we'd better go with this option instead.
What say we change things up again, all right?
Let's shift some things around if you don't mind.
I think we ought to mix things up a bit.
Let's try this on for size instead, OK?
A hideous rendition of a grizzled skeleton seems suitable decor.
This thought-provoking piece seems like a decent conversation-starter for the hall.
A nice floral arrangement ought to lighten up the mood a little bit.
I'm sure nobody's going to mind some lovely flowers there.
Back there, let's change the color theming up a little bit.
This color ought to suit the hall back there.
We should redecorate the hall back there like so.
This is the color suited for our hall back there.
Let's try this color on for size instead.
I'd like to see it in this color once again.
This color seemed to suit the hall quite well.
Let's change the colors up back there again.
For Cerberus, only the greatest bed will do.
This seems a suitably fine resting-pad for Cerberus.
Excuse me while I swap your bedding for you, boy.
Let's change the bedding up for Cerberus.
This other bedding seems a better fit.
Hard to decide which bedding type to choose.
A marble bust of some old man seems just the thing to liven this place up.
I think those columns still could use some sprucing up.
Was thinking it'd be good to change those columns up a bit.
Changed my mind about those columns there.
Let's go back to an older style for those columns.
Cerberus was never keen on playing ball, but on the other hand, who doesn't like a ball?
If Hypnos is going to be sleeping on the job, he ought to do it in the lap of luxury.
They say that only Heracles himself can lift these things? I'll take them, then!
The hall to Father ought to look more sinister, I think.
A bit more mood lighting in the main hall is certainly in order, isn't it?
These undead flower petals ought to add an extra touch of elegance I think.
Can't have too many undead flower petals around here.
Let's get some undead flower petals over there, posthaste!
I won't be needing these but anyone emerging from the Pool of Styx might like them I suppose.
Let's set some decadent old tombs right smack in the middle of the hall back there.
Should make my bedchambers a little more presentable I guess.
I have this crippling compulsion to commission objects I am never, ever going to sit on.
Always wanted my own entertainment table, and I can finally afford one, I suppose.
If some big light-refracting orb won't fill the lounge with revelry, I don't know what will.
The lounge could use a decent rug I think.
This stately rug should match the lounge decor.
The lounge's regulars might like this rug I guess.
A serviceable rug for a serviceable lounge.
The wretched broker has to stand all day... or float? Anyway, maybe this helps.
It can't be eaten, as I understand, but it can be displayed for all to see!
Cerberus won't touch these things, although some shades seem to enjoy them fine.
Think this rug's really going to tie the whole room together.
Let's take that down for now.
Let's pack that up for now.
